Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
ecoCompareNetlist(25.10)                              ecoCompareNetlist(25.10)

Name
       ecoCompareNetlist - Compares a specified netlist with the design in the
       database for structural or logical equivalence, and creates a file con-
       taining the differences found

Syntax
       ecoCompareNetlist

       [-help]

       -def <referenceFileName>[-logical]

       [-outfile <fileName>]

       [-outputPhysicalInstInFile <physicalInstFile>]

       [-referenceData {inMemory | external}]

       Compares a specified netlist with the design in the database for struc-
       tural or logical equivalence, and creates a file containing the differ-
       ences found.

       ecoCompareNetlist supports bus top-level port comparison.

        ecoDisableNetRenamingForFlatNetlist

       Global  variable  ecoDisableNetRenamingForFlatNetlist is introduced. If
       it is set to 1, there would not be any net renaming for  flat  netlist.
       Net  renaming will take place if net name is hierarchical and the terms
       it connects to do not fall under the same hierarchy or lies up  in  the
       hierarchy. Do set ecoDisableNetRenamingForFlatNetlist 1 before the eco-
       CompareNetlist command to disable net renaming for flat netlist.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -def <referenceFileName>
              Specifies  the name of the DEF file that Innovus uses to compare
              with the design.

       -referenceData [inMemory | external]
              Specifies the data from where the post-ECO netlist is to be com-
              pared.

              * inMemory compares the post-ECO netlist to the netlist in  mem-
                ory. inMemory is the default behavior.

              * external compares the post-ECO netlist to an external netlist.

       -logical
              Compares the netlists for logical equivalence.

       -outfile <fileName>
              Specifies  the  file  that  contains the differences between the
              specified DEF file and the design in the database.

              If the directory specified to save the file does not exist,  the
              tool  creates  the directory. For example, in the following com-
              mand if a/ does not exist, the tool will create it:

              ecoCompareNetlist -def test.def -outfile ./a/test.rpt

       -outputPhysicalInstInFile <physicalInstFile>
              When this option is specified, physical instance eco command  is
              also written to eco file, and the added physical instances names
              one per line are dumped into the <physicalInstFile> file.

Example
              * The following command compares the myFile.def file against the
                design, and writes the results to differences.file:

                ecoCompareNetlist -def myFile.def -outfile differences.file

Related Information
